1 for the same fiscal year for which the expenditures are determined.
2 The aggregate student membership number shall be the count of
3 students enrolled on October 1 or the school day closest to October
4 1 to whom school districts in the state provide a public education.
5 The aggregate current expenditures shall include without limitation
6 the following categories of expenditures:
7 1. Instruction provided by school district instructional staff;
8 2. Instruction provided through career and technology education
9 programs in comprehensive schools;
10 3. Instruction provided through concurrent classes that satisfy
11 graduation requirements;
12 4. Support services for students;
13 3. 5. Support services for instructional staff;
14 4. 6. Support services for general administration;
15 5. 7. Support services for school administration;
16 6. 8. Support services for business;
17 7. 9. Operation and maintenance of plant services;
18 8. 10. Student transportation services;
19 9. 11. Child nutrition services; and
20 10. 12. Enterprise services.
21 B. Aggregate current expenditures shall not include
22 expenditures for adult and community education, facilities
23 acquisition and construction services, debt services, property, and
24 other expenditures not related to the day-to-day operations.
